rComments: Professor Rada was amazing. He gave us the exercises that were very similar to the test.

No surprises on tests. Rada provides students with everything they need to succeed in his class. No need for the textbook considering he will provide lots of examples that are similar to test questions. This being said, his lecture notes are absolutely awful and youtube will be your best friend.

Honestly one of the best professors I've ever had. His notes are a little bit messy, so going to class is a must to understand the theory. He's very fair in his grading and his exams are very similar to past tests, so practice those. Overall a great professor. Shout out to the Punisher!
Great Prof!

If you do the assigned practice exams and just review the lectures after watching them, there's no reason why you can't do well. I find the pdfs that he shares incredibly study sources since they're so comprehensive. Do the work and you'll get the grade you desire
I love Rada man. Funniest dude. 11/10 prof. He doesn't write out each step when problem-solving during lectures (if that's not for u, don't take him) but he always finishes early

If you have taken calculus 1 in CEGEP or something equivalent, mat1300 is just a piece of cake. Catalin is an average prof. His course materials are useful and he really wants people to do well in this class. Tests are fair, as well. However, some students may need to get used to his accent.

He is nice and all but as of me and how I learn..I don't like his style of notes. very compact and confusing. if you follow his lectures and watch extra vids on your own time, then you might have a chance of passing. we used Mobius and I find it the most difficult website to work with. his tests can be brutal. I don't have time to finish them.

DO NOT TAKE HIS CLASS!!! I had always found math easy and this year I struggled. He is hard to understand and doesn't answer your question correctly. The answer key for practice are jokes, literally said "now guess!" as one of the answers so you don't even know if you're doing the work right. He rarely responds to emails timely and responses suck.

This prof is probably the best math teacher I've had and my favorite teacher this semester between all my courses. He tries his best in large meetings to make sure every one understands the material, answers all questions, and make you feel more comfortable with the material. He'll even put hearts on review sheets and crack jokes to make it fun!

He's a good prof, notes are structured a bit weird but you get used to it, and he really takes time to explain concepts and like drive it into your head. Would've gotten a better mark if I actually studied lol

Rada was awful. I ended up dropping his class cause he was so bad. His notes for the whole semester were all on one page and were hard to follow. He doesn't really explain how/why do to things. Also, he does not give nearly enough time on tests. Avoid if you can, or be prepared to teach yourself the whole course.
personally i liked this class and hes very charismatic. listens to his students which is really appreciated when it comes to wonky marking by TAs

professor Rada is disorganized and notes are hard to follow, all he does in the lectures is read word for word. creepy theme of being The Punisher?!? doesn't like to give partial points. final exam was hard!! GO TO THE DGDs. absolutely no feedback on any exam from TAs or him. only reason i passed was because i begged for a recorrection on each exam

Rada is super kind and actually listens to his students so that he can help them as much as possible on their exams. I have to say that his exams are quite tough and the grading is even tougher. As long as you do all of his practice then you should pass. He is a super caring guy though! Good luck to anyone taking his final exam! it's scary.

He is hilarious and listens to his students feedback. He really does care! I will say his notes are disorganized and hard to follow if you're not used to him - but honestly turned out to be beneficial because I had to pay extra attention to know what's going on. All in all great guy with TONS of practice questions available.

Prof Rada was a great prof. Beware he uses a word document instead of a powerpoint. He goes over lots of example in class but your grade is determined by only the 2 midterms and final. Midterms tended to be only 7 questions total. DGD is necessary and practice as much as you can for a good grade.

I took MAT1330 with Dr. Rada and liked him both times. Despite the constraints of online learning, he listened to student's feedback and improved. Each exam was run slightly different than the previous to run more smoothly. He's disorganized, but he keeps class entertaining and conveys the material well once you get used to his sayings.

I took MAT1330 with him. Absolutely hated it. But MAT1332 was a different story. Maybe it was because it took some time for him to get used to online learning. But the lectures were engaging and easy to follow. The tests were super fair (although I wasn't feeling the 60%-100% worth exam bc that was just stressful). All in all hilarious and awesome!

Dr. Rada is HILARIOUS. He is incredibly kind and opened up many office hours prior to exams. He even showed us his labradoodle, Zamfir. However, I wish he had imparted a conceptual understanding of the material. I know how to make a Jacobi matrix but not what a Jacobi matrix is and why it works. I do not believe I will retain the material.

wish he was my dad tbh. lots of cheesy jokes and talking about crying. teaching method is not the best but his tests are fair. could use a little more time on them and organizing his lectures better. very funny and accent is NOT bad like others make it out to be. humor makes up for the fact that youre learning calc.

I loved Prof Rada. He's incredibly funny during lectures and explains everything in detail. I found his class much easier than MAT1330. The exams are very fair and no trick questions. The only problem is that his notes are unorganized and take a while to decipher, but I would still take this prof again. Great guy
Don't even think about taking his class. Sure he's funny but AWFUL professor. Basically highlights a textbook pdf and makes you teach yourself

Dr. Rada is kind and hilarious. However, he is not clear as a lecturer, and I feel intimidated asking questions, as he acts a bit annoyed. I prefer Dr. Nevin's notes, which he posted in 'extra resources', to his notes, which are often unclear. Dr. Rada speaks with a heavy accent, which he cannot help, but to a subpar math student, this is hard.

Rada is super disorganized. His notes are one huge pdf that he reads off during lectures. I had to teach myself EVERYTHING. I thought that this class was so bad that I dropped Calc 2 cuz I was gonna have him again. He even yelled at ppl during a midterm, and no one could focus! Although I ended up doing well, I would not recommend him as a prof.

Hes so kind and funny. He definitely has an accent but not impossible to understand! Very approachable outside of class time and does his best to help his students. Not sure if it was the material or Rada himself, but the class does require some work! Not the easiest A for sure

On the final exam I asked him something along the lines of, "is this question asking for *this* or *that*?". To which his response was "yes". That should give you an idea of what Rada is like. Definitely avoid him for 1330.
pretty awesome. tests could use a little bit more time, but are fair.

Rada is a sweet person however this was the worst class I've ever taken. The notes were horrendous, basically a 100 page run on sentence. He didn't write anything out and just read off the document. The practice midterms were nothing like the real thing. Homework barely counts for marks so if you do bad on the tests goodluck boosting your grade.

Rada is a good guy. Calls himself The Punisher but is sweet. The course itself was poorly set up so that we had to enter our test answers into an unreliable software that ended up bringing everyone's grades down. And while Rada is decent, he isn't the best teacher and just reads off of his notes. Go to the dgds. I learned everything from them.

I didn't know that a professor could explain such simple topics w/ so much ambiguity and needless complexity. His teaching method is horrendous. It's impossible to learn math when someone just reads a doc word for word to you as a lesson. Ended up teaching myself through other online resources. The upside is that he's actually hilarious.

the WORST professor ever. I would repeat orgo 25615652 times instead of taking any easy A class with this professor. he never respond with more than 3 words email. His notes are useless. Neither his assignments nor his tests are reasonable. he never explains the examples. he doesn't even read all of them.

He jokes around too much that it became distracting. Attending lectures felt like a waste of time. Exams were way harder than the material provided in the class. Really really REALLY tough grader. Isnt quick with answering emails, and when he does its usually two words at best. Course felt like a mess. Please do urself a favor and avoid him lol.

Dr. Rada (the self-proclaimed "Punisher") has an interesting sense of humour and will keep class entertaining. He clearly knows the material well and is an effective teacher; he will often stress areas where students usually go wrong. His class is not organized at all though, so I recommend keeping yourself organized to do well in this course.

Goes through the examples so fast and it's really hard to follow along. Notes are an absolute disaster to read and Mobius is the worst program to exist. Gives practice midterms and finals that aren't even close to the level of difficulty of the test. Kinda funny guy but his teaching definitely needs some work.

very nice prof, midterms and Mobius assignments are unfair. I wish Mobius didn't exist, it ruined so many midterm marks and assignment marks as a result of formatting errors. His midterms are harder than the material from lectures, so expect the unexpected, they rly need to find a better way to grade midterms, it's super inefficient and unfair.

Absolutely horrible. Talks too fast during lectures, notes are crammed on a word doc, numerous typos and unnecessary comments, assignment questions are way harder than what is taught. Would not recommend, have never despised a prof so much.

The class was extremely disorganized, he jokes around too much that its so distracting. Assignments and exams are way harder and complicated than the examples during given lectures. Lots of mistakes in assignments. Takes a lot of time to answer emails and very unclear when doing so. Very tough grader! Please avoid him if u can.
Goes over the material quickly but his notes are stellar and easy to follow. Really cares about his students and helpful outside of lectures.

The worst prof Ive ever had. He provides unclear instructions and cannot teach for his life. He will not return emails in a timely fashion or at all. I did have him when all classes were online. He also refused to take my grades for the homework because I accessed the website via the URL not the bright space link. He is awful, avoid at all costs!!

I had the Punisher in Summer 2020 semester. I couldn't always make the lecture times but this man recorded a concise 30-40min lecture video, separate from the in class lecture, for every single lecture session. He does speak quickly in lectures since he's a smart professor, but having the video option lets you go back. He is a stellar online prof.

He has amazing notes that have a proper flow to them and are easy to understand. I took his class during summer, online. I did not attend online lectures and am doing really well just from teaching myself from his notes. He has weekly assignments and he gives you a whole week to finish them with no time limit. online midterm wasn't bad either.

I enjoyed his teaching style very much, but if you miss classes you might fall behind as he doesn't really have notes for you to look at on his site. If you learn from writing things down you will do very well in his class, but practice is necessary.
Dr. Punisher is one of the top 10 math profs at UO. A true gem. Remember, in class, he is Police Man, but on exam, he is Punisher.

Rada is a great teacher! Organized and really cares about his students. He does have an accent but it is really not that bad and you'll get used to it. After class, rewrite your notes and read them over again multiple times. The midterms are very similar to the in class questions so practice those a lot.

he mumbles through his lectures and he has a thick accent which makes it hard to understand whats going on. the mobius assignments are not reflective of what he teaches in class. his writing is really messy and he barely explains what he's teaching us
Very friendly and helpful during office hours
Love this guy! Make sure you try to learn the concepts before his lectures to fully understand and stay engaged during the lecture. Everything makes sense that way.

Professor Rada is definitely one of my favourite profs at uottawa. His lectures are incredibly thorough and he always takes the time to ensure hes explaining things well. He is super helpful if you have questions and always makes himself available/approachable in and out of class. pretty hard content but he makes it manageable & is super helpful.

Great Prof! Although, it took some time getting used to the fast pace of the lectures and heavy accent. Lecture content isn't posted online so going to class is important. Lots of homework so be prepared to do that. Fun facts: He calls himself "The Punisher" and recommends that you cry when you approaching a question.

Dr. Rada is a great prof! He is accessible outside of class and will answer any questions you have. He's also really funny and chill, and this makes the class entertaining. In class, material is presented quickly (due to the limited amount of time to cover material) so it is important to review your notes and practice. Overall, would take again!

Rada goes very fast through his lectures and examples. Most of the time it was hard keeping up with him in class, as he also has a thick accent. I do not recommend him if this is your first time taking the course.

I found him very difficult to understand when it comes to new topics... hes a funny professor and it seems like their people in my class are understanding ok but he goes very very fast in lectures and does lots of examples but not on all the types of questions you will see so I definitely struggled

Great prof; people might complain he's going too fast, but it's a summer class so his pace is effective in means of completing all the content before the final. He knows what he's doing and his midterms are very fair. He wants students to succeed, but students don't read their notes and blame him for their bad mark. He's actually a really good prof

Rada is very hilarious! He has an accent but as time goes by he'll become easier to understand. His expectations are clear and he does MANY examples in class so MAKE SURE you go to class and "practice them between 2-3am" as he says. Try to find some previous midterms online since he occasionally recycles questions. Overall a great teacher!

He goes VERY fast, but I noticed that I got better at understanding him and learning the content at a quicker pace. The assessments are easy and straightforward, but you have to put in effort, do the homework, and go to the DGDs. If you don't put in effort you will find the class challenging- so open the textbook, GO TO DGDs, and practice!!

Catalin is a funny teacher, although his humour can be slightly mean sometimes. The lectures provide a ton of examples, and the DGDs were incredibly useful, but still, there were questions on the tests that weren't in the textbook or taught about in class. A lot of people attended the afternoon class lectures afterwards.

Makes math lectures enjoyable. Makes sure to do lots of examples in class so you know exactly what to do for tests. He does go pretty fast so if you need a slow math prof probably don't choose him, but on the up side he does this so that a couple lectures are left completely for review problems. Has a decently thick accent so beware

I for one, find that he does not explain anything in class, you will ultimately teach yourself the theory by the posted notes, which are another teachers notes. He doesnt write all his steps, which makes it completely confusing. So far, the worst teacher I had at OttawaU. I dont recommend if you arnt naturally good in math and needs explaining

He is very funny and he knows it. His humor can be very SLIGHTLY demeaning sometimes (DONT BE SCARED its pretty casual) People who don't like him say he's fast. He is, but he is very accessible outside class, REPLIES EMAIL unlike many others. Covers a lot of examples instead of just throwing the theory. Active learning is practiced.

I give him five stars. He's my favorite teacher of all time. He knows a lot of Math and cares a lot about his students. I could see that he wants his students to succeed and tries his best to help them. Hes lectures are easy to follow and relevant. He tries to cover as many things as possible in a 2 hour course his explanations are clear.

I give him a 5 because he is quite the character to say the least. Very nice prof, funny too. I found his class a little hard to follow however because he goes so quick. Wish he provided more background information on the subject being taught. Overall good prof would take again. Also it should be noted he really changes the exams year to year.

I usually rate teachers very badly (they deserve it). However, Catalin isn't like the rest. At first I wasn't too excited by his teaching, then I started to know him and got used to him. He's funny, makes a boring subject interesting and most importantly, the exams are identical to the previous exams. Would take again.

He is hilarious, but awful as an actual teacher. Does not explain clearly, goes through examples way too quickly. And his writing is AWFUL. If you ask him a question, he is one of those people who just repeats what he previously said, he never explains more thoroughly, slowly, or from a new perspective or approach.

Knew his material well and managed to make the class quite enjoyable as he was extremely funny. Midterms were easy if you studied and did all the assignments however the final was brutal and very difficult so study a lot and ask many questions. Gives lots of examples and practice problems! Midterms are similar to the practice ones he gives!!

Idk why his rating is so high. He doesn't explain the concepts very well, and goes through practice problems so fast that it's hard to follow what he's doing. He doesn't post practice problems, previous exams or clear notes and his writing is barely legible. I found it hard to study for this course cause half the content isn't in the textbook.
Great examples and really helpful when you ask questions. Would recommend him for any 1302 student!

I am TERRIBLE at math. When I mean terrible, I mean I am prone to failing math classes. This is probably the first and the only math class where I was confident I could succeed. His notes are INCREDIBLY easy and clear to understand. He makes it so easy for you to succeed as well. The tests are all based on in class examples. BEST MATH TEACHER EVER!

He can be a little intense at first but he really cares about his students doing well. Gives class time to do a lot of helpful examples. I wouldn't sit on the ends of rows as he looks over you when youre working.

Really funny guy and you can tell he really cares. Gives time for people to work on examples during class. May pick on you to give an answer and look over your shoulder to see what youre doing. I waited to make sure he was my prof for calc 2!

Prior to taking MAT 1302 with Catalin Rada I was a C+ student in math at the most. his teaching style helped me realize how easy it is to understand math and my potential. Go to class, go to the DGD's, practice the previous exams he provides, and study a week before each midterm and you will, like me a C+ math student, get an A+ in the course. GL!
Best prof I've ever had. He is so funny, I wish he was my real father.

Dr Rada is AWESOME. He does a ton of examples that reflect what will be on the midterms/exam, and goes over it in a way that is super easy to understand. If you don't like your work being judged or work at a slower pace, don't sit in the aisle seats. He is a bit intimidating at first (calls himself the "punisher"), but he's a really friendly guy.
He is a funny guy but kinda scary at first. His teaching style did not work for me honestly and if given the chance, I wouldn't choose him again.

great prof for mat 1330!! his pace is slightly fast but he gives the best in class explanations and examples. Was always available right after lectures for detailed explanations and even though he seems a bit intimidating as he calls himself the "punisher" lol, he is super nice, understanding and easy to approach. would definitely recommend.

Good prof, very animated guy. Gives good in-class examples that closely resemble midterm; practice past midterms and especially DGD questions. Make sure to go to every class as his lecture notes are very important (online textbook is useless, and he doesn't post anything). I'm not great at math, but still received a decent grade. Recommended!
Terrible handwriting and notes, goes very fast, occasionally funny. Take his class BUT IT'S RISKY!

He covers a lot of examples in class, and the questions in his midterms and final closely resemble those problems. I practiced using midterms from other professors and thought Rada's evaluations were definitely easier (problems were very basic).  Also, don't sit on an aisle seat unless you're comfortable with him judging your work.

He is a decent prof who explains the material in class and provides time to actually practice the concepts. It helps determine where to practice. Exams are pretty straightforward. The only thing is that he was quite rude when I had some medical issues and was unaccommodating.

He's really funny. Very clear on what he will be putting on his exams. Barely used the online textbook, just practice past exams and you should do well. Great personality and a really nice guy. All our midterms were pretty straightforward and easy.
Definitely my favourite professor so far. The class itself can be difficult but he makes it a little bit more bearable.
I took both MAT1330 and 1332 with him. He gives many examples on class, a very nice guy.

He's an amazing prof, my favorite so far at Uottawa. His classes are difficult but if you attend class and participate you can do well. He gives time to actually try every problem in class, and then goes through them step by step to make make you understand. Textbook isn't mandatory as he gives all important info, but really helps.
He wants his students to succeed, and cares about them. Make sure to attend lectures and participate. Do the sample papers he uploads. One of the best profs I have had.
Amazing guy.

I thought he was pretty funny, which is really nice in a class as dry as calc. Stay on top of your work or you will get PUNISHED ! The notes are okay, but compared to the other calc profs in the school he is a star.

I found that he was rude and intimidating, which made me not even want to go to class. His accent made it harder to understand the material. Famous line he would say, "Who's crying now?" Didn't explain examples very well, or at all. In high school i got a 95% in calculus... didn't even pass his course. Avoid having him as a prof if you can!!

Dr. Rada (the Punisher) is a hilarious professor and his lectures are very clear. He is very clear of what he expects of students and you must study to pass! Do the practice problems and MEMORIZE THE NECESSARY FORMULAS. Very fair, he makes sure the students who try get what they deserve. Not a hard course, basically high school review mostly.

Rada is a great prof! He is also really funny (which is good because math can be a little dull!) He gives hints as to what is going to be on the midterms/exams and gives lots of examples! I really enjoyed my semester with him!
Great prof, lots of examples.

Rada was an amazing prof,  his lectures were straight forward and he gave lots of examples and gave us time to answer them before he did. He was sometimes funny and showed concern towards his students(he wanted everyone to understand it before moving on to another topic) he gave practice midterms and they were same, all you have to do is study

Rada is simply amazing, it was my second calculus 1 class(failed the first one, had a very bad prof(Wong)). He gives lots of practice questions in class and gives you time to try them before solving he solves them, he jokes are hilarious, he pretty much cares about his students, his practice test are exactly the same, his not a tough grader.

I hate math but when I took Calc I with Rada, he explained concepts in a way that helped me understand the majority of the course. He makes the effort to go over important examples with everyone  during class (3 minutes to try questions yourself which may not make for a low-key 90 minute lecture but in the end, you come to appreciate his methods.

Amazing prof. Gives practice test thats exactly the same, expect he changes the numbers. Lectures are a bit boring (FYI: its a math class, its not supposed to be fun), he gives lots of examples and gives you time to try them on your own in class. His simply amazing, would advice you take him.

I do not recommend.  Hard to understand, not helpful if you email him and  the worse  No matter how good you did on the first quiz and how good you did on practice exams, you fail fail the second midterm because the questions are 0 related to practice exam.  Yes i'm bitter.

This course was Cal 3. If you don't show up every day and take notes (and write down the examples done in class) you're screwed. If you DO show up and take notes though, it's easy. Accent's a little tricky at first, but it's easy to get past. Textbook is good for more problems, but he explains better than the book imo. He's funny as hell too.
Good guy and pretty funny. Useful and explains better than most other profs

Very underrated prof. Knows what he's doing and knows how to convey the material. Test are exactly what was shown in lectures. Funny guy even though some of his jokes can get a bit stale. One of the best profs I've had.

He is a nice guy, but he is extremely hard to understand. He does not post slides online. His notes that he writes on the blackboard are hard to follow and copy down. I studied off of another math profs notes and website. Try to avoid taking him as a prof. The course itself is okay if you do the practice midtermsexams, and study hard.

He is very funny, and his class/notes are extremely easy. He posts practice midterms/finals and the actual exams are based on that. As long as you do the suggested problems, you will have no struggle passing his course with a high mark.

Great Prof overall. No textbook required and gives great examples in class with several practice exams online. Very funny and makes lectures interesting. The class moves quickly so if you miss a lecture it is important to catch up as soon as possible. Rada is approachable and cares about his students. Highly recommended.
He is absolutely amazing! I enjoyed his class and his humour. He has a distinct style to make everything easier and is just cool in his attitude. One of my three fav profs ever!

He tries to be funny and sometimes achieves it - "You know I am the devil right?" But he is hard to understand, so I mostly rely on the textbook to teach me what I need to know. Grade wise, he is very fair and tells you exactly what you need to know to complete the assignments/exams.

Recommended only if you have taken this course with a previous better professor, but are retaking the course for whatever reason and already have a solid grasp of the material. This way his midterms will most likely be considerably easier compared to the ones in your previous course and you won't have to attend lectures.

You have to be at the top of your game from the very beginning of his class until the very end, because he is terrible at lecturing and the final exam will be absolutely brutal compared to the midterms (more than 3x as long with multiple choice questions that take up as much time as long answer questions). May never be 100% prepared for the final.

Very hard to understand sometimes because of his accent, but he is a funny prof. His midterms were very easy compared to the final exam, which I found quite difficult. He doesn't provide that many extra materials so don't skip the lectures.
Rada can be hard to understand at times but is a great Prof! His midterms are IDENTICAL format to the practice midterms he gives you. Study them and you will do well!

Very funny prof. Assignments are easy cheesy if you go to class and DGDs. The Exam is the same format as the practice exam he gives you. Really nice guy and accent isn't a learning barrier at all. Hate math but this guy makes it worth coming to class.

Funny proff, Class was surprisingly interesting compared to high school math. He answers all question and makes sure you understand. He is very knowledgeable. Exams/midterms were no surprises, Assignments marking  was strict tho
Tries to make math as interesting as he can for you, I liked his teaching.

At first I was really freaked out because I had a hard time understanding his accent but you get used to it. He is very clear and knows his stuff. Go to the DGDs if you are having trouble but overall I thought he was a very good prof and I did not mind going to his class at all, although some people did find it very difficult.

He knows his stuff but his lectures are not structured at all. He starts off slowly and then skips intermediate, sometimes crucial, steps when explaining, and then just keeps speeding up as the class goes by. The last  10-15 minutes are always the worst since it's when everyone gets lost. SWITCH OUT. I had to attend another class to pass the course

He is a very nice guy, but not an effective teacher. His accent is impossible to understand because he tends to mumble and speak unclearly. He also has very small writing and I found that going to class was not very helpful. Expect to rely on the textbook if you take this class.

First midterm and second midterm were almost same as the old exams that he posted in his website. However, the final exam was tooo hard. in my opinion, students should get good score in the first and second midterms, so they can get at least c beucase the fainl will be bad.

The funniest prof ever :D. He has an accent, but you get used to it overtime. His lectures are interesting and he gives similar assignment question on the exams, so be sure to revisit them. He doesn't take late assignments, so you better be early to hand in on time.

"f(x) is not a horse, it is a function. We must kill the function!" Really funny prof, good teacher. Marks fairly, the midterms and exams are just like the assignment and textbook questions. Don't hand anything in even a minute later than the deadline though, he won't accept it.

He was pretty great. I just started Calc II: Return of the Calc, and it the new teacher is not as good. His accent is hard to understand at first, and his writing is a little hard to understand, but most of what he teaches you makes sense, and after you do a few examples you know what he's talking about. He's a good teacher.

To start off, I hate Calculus. I only took this course because it's compulsory for my program. Professor Rada is extremely nice and very helpful if you talk to him. It's sometimes hard to understand his accent but he writes all his notes on the chalkboard so that's fine. Provides tons of examples! Exams were the same as assignments - DO THEM!

I LOVE HIM.He is my punsher!!!I took calc 1 and 2 with this guy waht ever i did i ended up in his class. he is really funny ....when it comes to exams and assignments you have to STUDY, which is good coz that's what his job is!!!i love him one of the best profs!!! thank you prof if you r reading this!!!:)

"they call me the punisher!" omg looved when he said that line! overall this guy is not like other profs and he loves to joke arround with students. very helpful and does so many examples in class. Remember to study past midterms and assignments. One of my fav profs and i loved going to class! Exam is tricky, you NEED to study to pass :)

He is a nice and humourous prof and makes calculus fun. He also gives us problems to  try in class. Yet I find that we really got to understand what he is saying since he rushes through the course like a Via train, and his writing is quite messy. also his appearance is not the best.

Really enthusiastic. Uses humor to keep the class interested. He explains concepts very thoroughly. Has a bit of an accent, but is not hard to understand (at least it wasn't for me). Fair assignments, midterms, and finals. Overall, he's a very good professor.

He is a nice guy , kind of hard to understand. Using the book is USELESS, for his first midterm it was exactlyyyyyyyyyy the same as and old assignment he posted so just do all the assignments old & new over and over and kinda try to memorize them and your fine. Final exam, was okay.. a bit hard, but fair.

Very funny guy. His first midterm was a complete review from high school, second was a bit harder, but he doesn't try to trick you. Oh and even if you're one minute late handing in his assignment he wont accept it. But, overall, his class is pretty enjoyable.

Don't get me wrong he's a nice guy. Unfortunately I can't understand a thing he's saying. I learned some of this material in high school, but when he explains it I cannot comprehend what in the world he is saying
RUSSEL BRAND ALL THE WAY

Hilarious. You end up going to class just to see what he will say next. All the midterms just use old assignment questions. Final exam hard but bell curves it so you have a chance. Make sure you "doo" the practice assignments, they will be on the miderms.
Good Guy.

Very funny prof!! His expressions are hilarious if you can get past the accent. Threatens to bring his whip into class if you are not quiet, and frequently "pulls functions from his belly". Midterms are tricky; expect some odd, foreign-looking questions. Not as "easy-cheesy" as he says it is! LOL
terrible
